value.name: 800 (number) - Wikipedia
value.snippet: 800 (eight hundred) is the natural number following 799 and preceding 801. It is the sum of four consecutive primes (193 + 197 + 199 + 211). It is a Harshad number, an Achilles number and the area of a square with diagonal 40.

value.name: The 800 – Wikipedia
